permalink: /Psychological Nature Poetry (20th century)/Adrienne Rich/Adrienne Rich - River Stories
---

Each river holds its story like a breath,
carrying the pasts of every stone,
I walk beside the banks, opening
my heart to the cries of the depths.

There is a quietude,  
I find a space to dwell,  
a canvas where the water whispers,
beyond what words could tell.


- Adrienne Rich
